                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As saddened as I am by today's childishness, this is a damn good thing and a useful point of information, and, dare I say, a very important distinction between WoW and a certain unnamed game.
<br />

<br />
This post suggests that Blizzard and co. intend to punish accounts that are buying and delete accounts that are selling gold/items and characters.  This is 100% more than the management at a certain unnamed game ever did, and I don't know very many people who viewed the institution of ebayed characters, money, and items as something that improved the community of a certain unnamed game...</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=646635" target="_blank" class="postlink">Saediien Iluvatri</a>
<br />
Retired Coercer of The Rathe
<br />
