<br />
Without droppable items and gear, there is no in game economy. There is no real reason to have money in the first place. If you did not mean to include every item in the game as being no drop, then whatever you do not include will be sold out of game for real money.
<br />

<br />
As far as catching someone selling for real money, or selling accounts...I agree there is no way to determine this. Sure, you can track player transactions and transfers of in game items, and identify people who appear to be engaing in the practice...however, trading in game is not illegal. Transactions within the game, however frequent or however out of wack the trade is...offers no real proof of said activity.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic">That is all I have to say about that! - Forest Gump</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
